Allows for one or more operation to be applied to a set of objects at runtime, decoupling the operations 
from the object structure.The pattern should be used when you have distinct and unrelated operations to
perform across a structure of objects.   

The arguments and return types for the visiting methods needs to be known in advance, 
so the Visitor pattern is not good for situations where these visited classes are subject to change. 
Every time a new type of Element is added, every Visitor derived class must be amended.  